FBIS3-60821 "jptot001__l94069" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL IDF Said To Call Off Hunt for Fatah Murderers Qatif Settlers To Pursue Fatah `Murderers' TA2712123893 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 27 Dec 93 p 2 TA2712123893 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [ITIM report] [Excerpt] Settlers in the Qatif Bloc have decided to establish a body that will capture terrorist murderers who are members of the Fatah organization. This comes in the wake of the report, first released by ITIM, that the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has called off its pursuit of Fatah murderers. One of the settlers told an ITIM correspondent that if the IDF cannot do its job, the settlers, whose friends have been murdered, cannot sit by without bringing the murderers to justice. [passage omitted]
